		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I would love to work on games for a living, but my last 2 attempts failed. It seems more like winning the lottery if your game is successful, regardless of how fun it is.<br /><br />I have since given up and moved back into back-end systems development and testing and am doing quite well for myself again.<br />It just seems like a ton of work with very little return, other than the fact that you get to work on games.

		

		</td>
